GDIB works as a non-rocking-chair, i.e. dual-ion battery by utilizing the reversible intercalation of anions into the graphite cathode during charging (oxidation of graphite network). On the anode side, metal electroplating, intercalation, or alloying reactions might take place. The corresponding half-reactions during charging can be described as follows:1Oncathode:xA-+Graphite↔Graphite(A-)x+xe-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
