We would like to emphasize that currently there exists no common practice for reporting cell-level energy density for various DIBs. Many reports focus exclusively on the specific charge storage capacity of individual electrodes. In our case, where potassium electroplating occurs on the anode, the cell-level capacity can be expressed as follows (see Supplementary Notes 1 and 2 for details):4GravimetricCcell=Fx[electrolyte]CcFx[electrolyte]+Ccρ⋅103Ahkg-1,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
